    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-12-29T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-12-29T16:00:00-05:00" n="859"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d859">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">681.003/102: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Diplomatic Agent and Consul General at Tangier</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Blake</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-12-29T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 29, 1934—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>16. For Blake. You are requested to visit Madrid immediately to participate in
                    the discussions between Ambassador Bowers and the Spanish Foreign Office
                    regarding (1) the situation of the United States in the Spanish Zone as reported
                    in your 944 of June 1;<note n="92" xml:id="d859fn1">Not printed.</note> (2) the
                    situation resulting from the breaking down of the <hi rend="italic">modus
                        vivendi</hi> in the Spanish Zone as reported in your 909 of January 26<note
                        n="92" xml:id="d859fn2">Not printed.</note> and the question of settlement
                    of outstanding American claims in exchange for recognition of the Spanish
                    protectorate; (3) the Spanish attitude with respect to the French proposals for
                    a modification of the customs regime and presentation of the viewpoint of this
                    Government upon the subject as heretofore outlined in telegrams addressed to
                    you.</p>
                <p>Please report by cable date of your arrival in Madrid.</p>
                <p>Transportation expenses and per diem to Madrid and return authorized subject
                    Travel Regulations. Also authorized Chargé $6.00 per diem at Madrid. Submit
                    estimate.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
